  "time_ut": 1656636335,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dc2\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dbb \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 IMF \u0dc3\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "IMF is ready to support Sri Lanka in difficult times",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The delegation of the International Monetary Fund on a visit to Sri Lanka says that it reaffirms its commitment to support Sri Lanka in this difficult time in accordance with the policies of the International Monetary Fund.",
        "An International Monetary Fund (IMF) delegation headed by Mr. Peter Brewer and Mr. Masahiro Nozaki arrived in Colombo from June 20 to 30, 2022 to discuss the IMF support for Sri Lanka and the comprehensive economic reform program of the authorities. This has been said.",
        "They say that they reaffirm their commitment to support Sri Lanka in this difficult time in accordance with the policies of the International Monetary Fund. They also say that the staff team and the authorities have made significant progress in defining a macroeconomic and structural policy package.",
        "Discussions continue with a view to reaching a staff-level agreement on the IMF Extended Fund Facility (EFF) arrangement in the near term, and adequate financial assurances from Sri Lanka's creditors that debt sustainability will be restored for Executive Board approval, as the public debt has been assessed as unsustainable. It is also indicated that it is necessary.",
        "Also, as revenues remain low, long-term tax reforms are urgently needed to achieve these goals, and other challenges that need to be addressed include controlling rising inflation, addressing tight balance of payments pressures, reducing corruption risks and initiating growth-enhancing reforms. The IMF statement added."
      ],
